tags.name: King Street
tags.note: Pedestrian Zone. No vehicles. Except for permit holders and for loading Midnight-10 am, 4pm-Midnight. No waiting at any time.
tags.note2: Though the sign at the west end of the street states "No vehicles" in text it actually has a no motor vehicles symbol.

tags.name: Railway Street
tags.note: While there appears to be widespread perception this street is one way there is no actual signage in the street to reflect this.
There are multiple transverse strips of what looks like concrete but may be stone

tags.fixme: may need adjustment after building work

tags.note: In May 2018 the surface of the steps was asphalt sheet - no doubt over wood as previously tagged - while the structure of the bridge assembly is steel
Please see note on corresponding steps, though I didn't survey these ones in May 2018
Effectively one step up, then one step down from either direction, ie a ridge
I'm sure there's room for improvement of tagging here
tags.note_2: It's actually just a "cycling allowed on the pavement" bit of road. There is no separate footway.
